<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="463" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1769,2039]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1769,1795]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Remarks:</emphasis>
This mounted pair, a male and a female, have 
<emphasis box="[791,894,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
‘(
<typeStatus box="[805,880,1770,1796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Typus</typeStatus>
)’
</emphasis>
written on their labels (with parentheses; 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1359,1383]" captionTargetBox="[165,1429,190,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[158,1430,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Labels of type specimens (maintained and refuted) in the NHMO Bird Collection described by A.B. Meyer. a) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (original Dresden label); b) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (NHMO label); c) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64131 (original Dresden label); d) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64132 (original Dresden label); e) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64130 (original Dresden label); f) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64228 (original Dresden label); g) Artamus Musschenbroeki NHMO-BI-68621 (original Dresden label)." pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Figure 3c and 3d</figureCitation>
), but this is not mentioned in the letter that accompanied the specimens when they arrived at the museum (
<figureCitation box="[159,254,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[191,1396,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Facsimile of parts of the letter from A. B. Meyer to R. Collett 11 July 1886, including the section about the content of the shipment sent to Oslo the same day, plus the header and signature parts." pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). While these labels are in a different style than the labels of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[952,1212,1839,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ptilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis box="[952,1212,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Ptilopus flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1228,1337,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1359,1383]" captionTargetBox="[165,1429,190,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[158,1430,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Labels of type specimens (maintained and refuted) in the NHMO Bird Collection described by A.B. Meyer. a) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (original Dresden label); b) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (NHMO label); c) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64131 (original Dresden label); d) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64132 (original Dresden label); e) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64130 (original Dresden label); f) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64228 (original Dresden label); g) Artamus Musschenbroeki NHMO-BI-68621 (original Dresden label)." pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Figure 3a</figureCitation>
) and the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[151,435,1873,1899]" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Geoffroyus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="timorlaoensis">
<emphasis box="[151,435,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
female (
<figureCitation box="[537,647,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1359,1383]" captionTargetBox="[165,1429,190,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[158,1430,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Labels of type specimens (maintained and refuted) in the NHMO Bird Collection described by A.B. Meyer. a) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (original Dresden label); b) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (NHMO label); c) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64131 (original Dresden label); d) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64132 (original Dresden label); e) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64130 (original Dresden label); f) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64228 (original Dresden label); g) Artamus Musschenbroeki NHMO-BI-68621 (original Dresden label)." pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Figure 3f</figureCitation>
), they are very similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[1088,1373,1873,1899]" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Geoffroyus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="timorlaoensis">
<emphasis box="[1088,1373,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male (
<figureCitation box="[159,267,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1359,1383]" captionTargetBox="[165,1429,190,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[158,1430,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Labels of type specimens (maintained and refuted) in the NHMO Bird Collection described by A.B. Meyer. a) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (original Dresden label); b) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (NHMO label); c) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64131 (original Dresden label); d) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64132 (original Dresden label); e) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64130 (original Dresden label); f) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64228 (original Dresden label); g) Artamus Musschenbroeki NHMO-BI-68621 (original Dresden label)." pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Figure 3e</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Musschenbroeki" authorityName="Musschenbroeki Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[329,612,1908,1934]" class="Aves" family="Artamidae" genus="Artamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[329,612,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Artamus Musschenbroeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[626,737,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1359,1383]" captionTargetBox="[165,1429,190,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[158,1430,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Labels of type specimens (maintained and refuted) in the NHMO Bird Collection described by A.B. Meyer. a) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (original Dresden label); b) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (NHMO label); c) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64131 (original Dresden label); d) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64132 (original Dresden label); e) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64130 (original Dresden label); f) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64228 (original Dresden label); g) Artamus Musschenbroeki NHMO-BI-68621 (original Dresden label)." pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Figure 
<quantity box="[707,737,1908,1934]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), and to labels written by Meyer and found on other specimens currently in the SNSD collection. They, hence, apparently represent a 
<emphasis box="[926,935,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">‘</emphasis>
prettier’ version of Meyer’s handwriting, and also these labels are therefore considered to be original. 
<emphasis box="[780,863,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">‘Typus’</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[917,1108,1977,2004]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">‘Mus. Dresd. 86’</emphasis>
, however, seem to have been added after the main text, probably by two different persons, and may likely have been added at NHMO.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
The original description of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, A. B." box="[647,786,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="917 - 918" refId="ref15320" refString="Meyer, A. B. (1882) On a new species of Eclectus from the Timorlaut Islands. Proceedings of the Scientific Meetings of the Zoological Society of London, 1881, 917 - 918. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1881. tb 01348. x" type="journal article" year="1882">Meyer 1882</bibRefCitation>
) was, however, based on a single female specimen, which consequently should be regarded as the 
<typeStatus box="[612,714,185,211]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">holotype</typeStatus>
. This was at the MTD (now SNSD) but was lost during WW2 (C6051; 
<bibRefCitation author="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C." box="[252,503,220,246]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="233 - 316" refId="ref14237" refString="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2004) Verzeichnis der Typen der Vogelsammlung des Museums fur Tierkunde in den Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 54, 233 - 316." type="journal article" year="2004">Eck &amp; Quaisser 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Consequently, neither of the specimens in the NHMO collection can be the true 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,255,281]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">holotype</typeStatus>
of this taxon. Most likely these specimens represent a similar case to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1882" box="[1065,1257,255,281]" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Eclectus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="roratus" subSpecies="riedeli">
<emphasis box="[1065,1257,255,281]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">E. roratus riedeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NMW 50.145) in NHMW, which was included in the type catalogue by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pelzeln, A. &amp; Lorenz, L." box="[789,1068,289,316]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="37 - 62" refId="ref15941" refString="Pelzeln, A. v. &amp; Lorenz, L. v. (1888) Typen der ornithologischen Sammlung des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums. IV. Theil (Schluss). Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 3 (1), 37 - 62." type="journal article" year="1888">Pelzeln &amp; Lorenz (1888)</bibRefCitation>
and there described as a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">‘typical specimen’</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[278,516,324,350]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">‘typisches Exemplar’</emphasis>
) but later dismissed as a type by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schifter, H." box="[889,1063,324,350]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="63 - 73" refId="ref16437" refString="Schifter, H. (1990) Dr. Adolf Bernhard Meyer und die Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 46 (3), 63 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">Schifter (1990)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
While no 
<typeStatus box="[309,401,359,385]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">neotype</typeStatus>
, to our knowledge, has been assigned for this taxon, we refrain from doing so with reference to article 75.2 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation author="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[458,1148,393,420]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" refId="ref14975" refString="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
No collecting date was provided for these specimens, but the same reasoning as explained for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ptilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Ptilopus flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above has been applied. However, as the shipment containing these specimens was sent from Dresden in 
<date box="[151,264,499,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" value="1886-07">July 1886</date>
, and they are not part of the 
<typeStatus box="[584,632,499,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">type</typeStatus>
series, they may have been collected as late 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, A. B." box="[1132,1222,499,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" refId="ref15425" refString="Meyer, A. B. (1886) Letter from A. B. Meyer to R. Collett 11 July 1886, National Library of Norway. Ms. fol. 4339. Available from: https: // urn. nb. no / URN: NBN: no-nb _ digimanus _ 180183 (accessed 06.02.2022)." type="url" year="1886">as 1886</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
